"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Lovestick was born about 1305, in England, United Kingdom. She married William Lovestick in 1337, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1338, in Hallon, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1305–Aft 1338":"umbes 1305–pärast 1338","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1338–1386":"1338–1386","1305–1338":"1305–1338","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1369":"1369","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","Aft 1338":"pärast 1338","Abt 1305":"umbes 1305","England":"England","Hallon, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hallon, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1305–Aft 1338":"noin 1305–1338 jälkeen","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1338–1386":"1338–1386","1305–1338":"1305–1338","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1369":"1369","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","Aft 1338":"1338 jälkeen","Abt 1305":"noin 1305","England":"England","Hallon, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hallon, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1305–Aft 1338":"environ 1305–après 1338","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1338–1386":"1338–1386","1305–1338":"1305–1338","1338":"133